    "discriminators": [
     "Paper friction: sustained contact noise — high sustain_ratio, low crest, continuous flux, no single onset.",
     "Never front-loaded like IMPACT; more continuous and higher-centroid than MOVEMENT.",
     "Sliding or scraping paper: a continuous bright hiss-rasp, the softest and highest-centroid friction in the material set.",
     "Lower onset_rate and much smoother than PAPER-HANDLE's crumple crackle; lower level and shorter than PAPER-RIP's tear.",
     "Compare METAL-FRICTION (a screech with ringing partials) and WOOD-FRICTION (mid-centroid, gritty): paper friction is pure high-frequency noise with harmonicity near zero."
    ],
