    "discriminators": [
     "Crumple / crinkle / page-turn: dense stochastic micro-onsets — the highest onset_rate and the most extreme high_band_energy in the whole material axis. This is what 'crackly' measures as.",
     "Near-zero ring and almost no energy below 200 Hz separate it from CLOTH-MOVEMENT (mid/low, damped, far fewer micro-onsets) and from PLASTIC-MOVEMENT (brighter than cloth but with real ring and a rattly, lower onset_rate).",
     "Nothing like METAL (ring) or WOOD (thud): paper has no resonant body at all.",
     "Overlaps OBJECTS-BOOK by definition in the UCS explanation; text must break the tie."
    ],
